      "intro": "If your loved one needs daily help with bathing, dressing, or medication management but you want them to stay at home, Louisiana's Adult Day Health Care Waiver provides supervised care at local centers Monday through Friday. Your loved one receives medical oversight, structured activities, nutritious meals, and socialization during daytime hours while you work or handle other responsibilities.\n\nBecause this waiver covers comprehensive day services under Medicaid, your loved one gets professional health monitoring, cognitive exercises, and social interaction without the cost of private adult day care. Income limit: $2,163/month for a single person in 2025, though you can spend down excess income on medical expenses.\n\nThe program operates on a priority waitlist system, hospital discharge patients and those at immediate risk get served first, while others may wait months to years depending on local demand. Centers operate during business hours only, so you'll need coverage for evenings, nights, and weekends.",
